Package: EPA.MACT.floor.UPL
Type: Package
Title: UPL calculations for MACT floor standards
Version: 0.1.0
Author: 
  person(
    "Ludda", "Ludwig",
    email = "Ludwig.Ludda@epa.gov",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2873-479X")
  )
Maintainer: Ludda Ludwig <Ludwig.Ludda@epa.gov>
Description: National Emission Standards for Hazardous Air Pollutants (NESHAP) 
  Maximum Achievable Control Technology (MACT) floor analysis.
  Functions for determining top performers amongst a sample population 
  of emissions data for Emission Guidance (EG) and New Source Performance Standards (NSPS). 
  Functions for determining the best distribution to represent the emissions data 
  and calculating the corresponding Upper Predictive Limit (UPL). Functions for 
  comparing the observation data density to prediction distribution density.
